            <h2>Reflexology</h2>
            <p>Reflexology is an ancient practice originating from Egypt, India, and China and made its way to the western world in the early 1900s. Reflexology is a technique that applies gentle pressure generally to your feet. It aims to bring about a state of relaxation and help the body's own healing process. Reflexology works in a similar way to acupressure and acupuncture and the main theory behind reflexology is that all the systems and organs of the body are mapped or reflected in smaller peripheral areas such as on the zones of the feet (and even the hands, ears and face). By working these areas the aim is to restore balance facilitating the body's natural ability to optimize health and well-being. This treatment is extremely relaxing and allows you to switch.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="reiki" class="container">
        <div class="container-header">
          <div class="copy">
            <h2>Usai Reiki</h2>
            <p>“Reiki” is Japanese for 'universal life energy.'' This tradition was founded by Mikao Usui in the early 20th century and is an energy healing technique that promotes relaxation, reduces stress and anxiety through gentle touch. Treatment is given by placing hands gently on different areas of your body holding each position as energy flows. The hand positions are non-intrusive and are sometimes varied to allow Reiki energy to flow to areas where it is specifically needed. You may feel sensations such as heat, cold, tingling, see colours, feel emotional or you may feel very little. There is no right or wrong way to experience Reiki. Many people experience a sense of well-being and relaxation, some people even fall asleep. You take what you need from it, the practitioner simply is a channel for the energy to flow through. Most people feel very relaxed and at peace after a Reiki treatment.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="eft" class="container">
        <div class="container-header reverse">
          <div class="copy">
            <h2>EFT</h2>
            <p>Emotional Freedom Technique is a meridian based therapy that draws on the traditional chinese medicine practice of acupuncture (without the needles). It involves tapping key acupressure points on the hands, face, and body with your fingertips while focusing on uncomfortable feelings or concerns, and using positive affirmations to neutralize those feelings. Lightly tapping these points helps to move energy around the system. This process reduces stress and anxiety, increases mind body awareness and fosters cognitive shifts. EFT can be applied to anxieties, fears, phobias, anger, low self-esteem, PTSD, relationship issues, painful memories and much more.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

